	   <tr><td colspan=2>Aloha all and well met--<br><br>Had to respond to the chap above about the ranger aggro and usefulness of this weapon.<br><br>First, I agree with Tannah on the aggro management piece.&nbsp;&nbsp;Although I am not in the most well equipped guild on drinal, our warriors are well equiped enough to maintain the aggro.  The weapon should not be allocated purely on if the ranger will get aggro or not.<br><br>Second point of interest is the DOT itself.  540 DOT spaced out over 21 ticks is not a really significant amount of damage when fighting mobs with the huge hit points that you find in the end game.<br><br>Third point is the lovely set of stats, and the incredible Damage delay ratio.  By this point in the game, many rangers are begining to sheath their epics in lieu of weapons that have either better stats, or damage delay ratios.  Againt the High AC mobs that we are facing in the Luclin encounters, we are finding that despite all the praise given to EQ+AM3, ranger DPS is greatly reduced on a lot of the mobs -- similiar results for our fast flashy dueal weilding weapons.  I have recorded far to many min damage hits for 1 than I care to recall.<br><br>So, perhaps rangers ought to be considered for the high damage 2 handed weapon, coupled of course with a haste item to replace our old swiftwinds.<br><br>Please note, I am not attempting to snatch this fine weapon away from our fellow melee -- this would be a super weapon for both Palys as well as the SKs and the non MT warrior  [ although the 125 mana is kinda lost hon him :-( ]  I a mearly attempting to refute the previous silliness and present an additional side to the &quot;WE HATE RANGER CLAN&quot; point of view that pervades these threads.  I am happy for whomever is awarded this fine weapon.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Huntress Samanthie Snowheart<br>Half-elf Karana Warder of Surefall Glade<br>65 seasons and more -- sniffing the trails of Norrath<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=369799" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=369799</a></td></tr>
