	   <tr><td colspan=2>No way would a ranger die wielding the Greatsword.&nbsp;&nbsp;Say you could get the delay down (with massive haste) to like 20 ... that is most likely slower than the MT's hasted one handers.  For purposes of aggro, it's not the damage that gets the mob's attention, but the shortest delay weapons doing the most hits per round.  A couple of fast weapons is what good tanks use to maintain reliable aggro.  Of course, if the PROC on the weapon generates a lot of aggro, then there may be some concern.<br><br>No way a ranger should get ahold of this weapon, unless all the paladins / shadowknights present have even crazier weapons ... the weapon's like 60 damage / 42 delay most of the time, for Chrissakes :)  I love big 2hders, but would probably keep very quiet if this one dropped for our raid force (unless for some reason we had a severe shortage of pallies/sks).<br><br>Khemosaabe &quot;Tonto SPAM&quot; Longbow (of Cazic Thule server)<br>Lvl 56 Ranger and Slayer-of-Bunny-Wabbits<br>&quot;H-H-Hey Ralphie Boy!&quot;<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
